<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 27 at 12:20PM EDT  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of
eastern Surry, Stokes, Yadkin and south central Patrick Counties
through 1245 PM EDT...
At 1219 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from Collinstown to Crutchfield. Movement was
southeast at 20 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Torrential rainfall is also occurring
with these storms and may lead to localized flooding. Do
not drive your vehicle through flooded roadways.
Locations impacted include...
Elkin...
Fairview...
Yadkinville...
Pilot Mountain...
Boonville...
East Bend...
and Danbury.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
